The paper deals with a fundamental resource allocation problem and presents results related to mechanism design, which are typically studied in the game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of preferences and allocation algorithms, which are relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and strategyproofness of allocation mechanisms, which are topics of interest in the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
